    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** serving as our primary offensive engines, both posting strong efficiency scores north of 79 against a favorable matchup with Javier Assad. **Trea Turner** is the premier play of the day, leveraging his elite leadoff position and a 19% SP skill advantage to anchor our stolen base goals. **Kyle Schwarber** provides the complementary power profile, with his elite 0.402 xwOBA providing a high floor regardless of the dynamic platoon fluctuations. **Caleb Durbin** and **Josh Smith** also command respect in our starting nine; **Caleb Durbin** benefits significantly from a top-of-the-order bump and neutral platoon splits, while **Josh Smith** is buoyed by a substantial +15% SP skill advantage against Luis Severino.\n\nOur toughest bench decision involved **Carson Benge**, who narrowly missed the cut at 36.52. While he possesses latent upside, the combination of an elite arm in Justin Wrobleski and the restrictive nature of an assumed #7 spot in the order kept his efficiency below our 40-point threshold for active duty. We remain cautious with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Victor Scott II**; while their speed is vital to our scarcity-driven strategy, both face difficult situational hurdles today\u2014**Pete Crow-Armstrong** is fighting against a 3.02 xERA arm, and **Victor Scott II** is hampered by a bottom-of-the-order assignment. With several high-impact bats like **Christian Yelich**, **Junior Caminero**, and **Kazuma Okamoto** currently inactive due to scheduling gaps, we are leaning heavily on our top-tier veterans to sustain our Roto standing until these depth pieces return to the lineup.",
